Overall happiness can be understood as the average score of various factors that contribute to a country's well-being, such as GDP per capita, life expectancy, and social support; Happiness scores are typically measured on a scale from 0 to 10, with higher scores indicating greater happiness; 
The happiness rank is determined by the average happiness score of each country over the years, with the highest score ranked first; 
The query considers all available data, including the latest year's happiness score for each country.
